Having quantified these terms, it is possible to determine the exergetic efficiency that is defined as the ratio between the production of useful energy and the consumption of exergy, or even the ratio between the exergetic input and output. Besides, the exergetic efficiency can be calculated as a function of the destruction of exergy. The exergetic efficiency characterizes the performance of a system or component of the system from thermodynamic point of view. Such characterization is somewhat subjective, in a sense that it possesses various definitions in literature. These may be divided in two main groups: 
