				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$^\circ$$\end{document}C. Thus, a system of heat exchangers could be implemented to adjust the temperature, aiming for maximum syngas into ethanol conversion. Another way to improve the exergetic efficiency would be adjusting number of compressors and heat exchangers. This way, the mass streams would not suffer harsh alterations of variables such as pressure and temperature.

